# DDS-SW
Firmware and Support Utilities for the DDS
This git repo documents the firmware for the Microchip PIC16F628A-IP
micro-controller used to to control the TTL DDS. The firmware is written
in assembler language that is assembled with the public domain PIC
assembler assembler (gpasm). On Debian based systems this assembler can
be installed using: apt install gputils.

File            Description
----            -----------
DDS.ASM         firmware's source code
DDS.lst         assembled firmware listing
DDS.hex         Intel Hex Image for device
freqcalc.py     tuning word calculator
IntelHex.py     used to generate an Intel Hex
                file for the sin() ROM
SIN.ITX         sin() function IntelHex ROM image

